comment: Add warning about TitlePageIndicator's adapter requirements.
Fix name in read me file. Stupid nano...
Make sure bold is pulled from the correct attribute.
Add proper centering so we can eliminate the wrapper layout.
Styling overhaul. Allow styles to be specified as theme attributes.
Move defaults into their own resource file so they can be reference in the code and in the default style.
Error if ViewPager is assigned to a CirclePageIndicator without an adapter.
Fix orientation bug with fragment re-instantiation.
Rename flow width to page width.
Add snap attribute to circle indicator which will force the indicator to always exist in the current page only.
Add getters and setters to all configurable attributes.
Allow specifying the current page directly on the indicator. This allows for proper configuration of a default page. Samples included.
Snap page needs its own index because of how the index is reported in onPageScrolled.
Add underline style which does not yet work.
Add shorthand for binding and setting initial page.
Support left/right clicking on the circle view to control paging. Closes #2.
Support left/right clicking on title views for paging. Closes #1.
Tweak to how click-paging is handled. We now only rely on the scrolled listener for positional updates. Closes #7.
Style tweaks and some minor method call caching.
Only count indicator height if it is enabled.
Add configurable padding between title text and indicator.
Add getter and setter for footer indicator padding.
Use floats for calculation since we are dealing with different densities.
Use internal touch event rather than being our own touch listener.
Inherit directly from View since we did nothing with TextView.
Change footer indicator padding to just be footer padding.
Add theming section to read me.
Fix bug of not setting the paint when we change the footer line height.
Add circle stroke width as an option.
Update the footer indicator paint when footer color is set programmatically. Refs #12.
Add support for fading the selected title text color.
Update change log and bump version to 1.0.1.
Allow padding between title and top of view to be specified for title page indicator.
Fix for issue where extra space would be drawn below footer line.
Add orientation support to the circle indicator.
Update change log for vertical circles.
Add methods to trigger invalidation when the data set changes. Closes #11.

Only act on onPageSelected when not scrolling or CirclePagerIndicator is set to snap to next page. This will make the PageIndicator react correctly when notifyDataSetChanged is called on the PagerAdapter, as well as stop it from reacting to onPageSelected during a scroll.
Update change log for SimonVT's fixes.
Add base sample activity which allows for adding and removing pages on-the-fly as well as for selecting a random page out of the current set.
Move package out of 'sample' to prepare for market deployment.
Link to app on Android Market.
Change package and maven descriptor to use `com.viewpagerindicator`.
Update readme to new package and artifact.
Move layouts to new package and update vertical view pager.
Update market app link to point to new package.
Use r4 of the compatibility lib
I like these defaults better. If you don't, make your own style!
Update compat lib binaries to r4.
Delete the DirectionalViewPager sample. That library is being left behind (for now) in development.
Port @SimonVT's title indicator drag patch to the circle indicator.
Import ABS 4.x's scrollable tab implementation. Currently onMeasure and onLayout are broken though...
Fix'd. Just need to remove dependency on explicit content height.
Update change log for new tabbed indicator.
Add sanity checks for unbound pagers and empty adapters. Closes #24.
Bump the version of ALL THE THINGS!
Correct the example maven dependency to include <type>apklib</type>
Change default title indicator style to 'underline' with some more sane defaults.
Optimize the title indicator measuring. Allow for all width modes. Refs #35.
Add typeface methods to title indicator. Refs #39.
Update dependency to use r6 compat lib. Refs #40.
Fix sample imports. Bump version to 2.2.2.
Give Superclass chance to handle Touch Events
Fix poor quality selected title (selected title has been drawn twice)
Update binaries to r6. Something wicket this way comes.
Use dp since we cannot appropriately react to scaling yet. Refs #49.
Allow superclass to attempt to handle touch events. Refs #45.
Removed the equal-sign which caused a FC when mCurrentPage was equal to bounds.size()
Revert "Removed the equal-sign which caused a FC when mCurrentPage was equal to bounds.size()"
Fix underline draw attempt being made on pages that might not exist. Refs #50.
Update circle indicators when the last page was removed.
Don't draw the current state if we are forcing another invalidation.
Fix dependencies to use android in central.
Fixed the issue when currentPage was set to 0 after device rotation. Works on all API versions
Use support library from Maven Central.
Added eclipse plugin configuration to parent POM
removed TitleProvider and use getPageTitle() from support library
Use built-in Android styles for textSize and textColor.
Update sample for new android namespaced attributes.
Do not repeatidly create new Path objects in onDraw().
Fixed a bug where the setCurrentItem doesn't change the viewpager's current item
Reuse single RectF across all onMeasure calls
Fix for lost content in sample app
`pom.xml` updates for central. New support lib.
Convert TitlePageIndicator to use CharSequence. Closes #79.
Don't load anything if we are in ADT's editor. Closes #57.
Reformat pom.xml. Add version to that Eclipse thing.
Properly check if fake drag is allowed before dragging. Closes #80.
Add 'Underline' indicator which mimcs the ICS Launcher.
Do not restrict alpha on selected color for underline.
Use position offset for page change calculations. Closes #58.
I have no idea how this happened...
Ensure we never fade the line if fading is disabled. Closes #99.
title.toString() drops the spans in a abstract CharSequence
Added ignore for command line build files
Left title overlaps current title with long text during right dragging. Fixes #101
remove mPagerAdapter variable and use mViewPager.getAdapter() instead
Do not tell people to implement TitleProvider. Closes #119.
Support setting background in styles. Closes #117.
Remove provided scope of support lib dependency in pom.xml.
groupId in child modules is optional. Mind = blown.
Allow drawing title underline on top. Closes #126.
Do not perform any ViewPager operations on ACTION_CANCEL.
Bump next version to 2.4.0. Start change log.
Add support for LinearLayout ICS-style dividers. Closes #125.
Show how to style tab text appropriately. Closes #71.
Consolidate adapters since TitleProvider is no longer around.
Bump version to 2.4.0. New screens showcase.
Version bump because I'm an idiot...
Show example of fading edges in TabPageIndicator.
